<refentry xml:id='RedirectFilter'
 xmlns='http://docbook.org/ns/docbook'
 version='5.0' xml:lang='en'
 xmlns:xsi='http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance'
 xsi:schemaLocation='http://docbook.org/ns/docbook http://docbook.org/xml/5.0/xsd/docbook.xsd'
 xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink'
 xmlns:xinclude='http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude'>
 <refmeta>
  <refentrytitle>RedirectFilter</refentrytitle><manvolnum>5</manvolnum>
 </refmeta>
 <refnamediv>
  <refname>RedirectFilter</refname>
  <refpurpose>rewrites Location headers</refpurpose>
 </refnamediv>
 <refsect1>
  <title>Description</title>
  <indexterm>
   <primary>Filters</primary>
   <secondary>RedirectFilter</secondary>
  </indexterm>
  <para>Rewrites Location headers on responses that generate a redirect that
  would take the user directly to the application being proxied rather than
  taking the user through OpenIG.</para>

  <para>For example, if OpenIG listens on
  <literal>https://openig.example.com:443/</literal> and the application it
  protects listens on <literal>http://app.example.com:8080/</literal>, then
  you can configure this filter to rewrite redirects that would take the user
  to locations under <literal>http://app.example.com:8080/</literal> to go
  instead to locations under
  <literal>https://openig.example.com:443/</literal>.</para>

  <para>The current implementation supports only HTTP 302 redirects.</para>

 </refsect1>
 <refsect1>
  <title>Usage</title>
  <programlisting language="javascript">{
     "name": string,
     "type": "RedirectFilter",
     "config": {
         "baseURI": string
     }
}</programlisting>
 </refsect1>
 <refsect1>
  <title>Properties</title>
  <variablelist>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><code>"baseURI"</code>: <emphasis>string, required</emphasis></term>
    <listitem>
     <para>The base URI of the OpenIG instance. This is used to rewrite the
     Location header on the redirect response.</para>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
 </refsect1>
 <refsect1>
  <title>Example</title>
  <programlisting language="javascript">{
     "name": "LocationRewriter",
     "type": "RedirectFilter",
     "config": {
         "baseURI": "https://openig.example.com:443/"
      }
}</programlisting>
 </refsect1>
